        <updateDate>2018-06-04T15:59:19Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><b>Korematsu-Takai Civil Liberties Protection Act of 2017</b></p> <p>This bill amends the federal criminal code to modify the detention authority of the United States. </p> <p>Specifically, it adds a provision to prohibit the detention or imprisonment of an individual based solely on an actual or perceived protected characteristic of that individual. A protected characteristic includes race, ethnicity, national origin, religion, gender, gender identity, and sexual orientation. </p>]]></text>
      </summary>
